curl -v POST https://api.sandbox.paypal.com/v1/payments/billing-plans \
-H 'Content-Type:application/json' \
-H 'Authorization: Bearer Access-Token' \
-d '{
  "name": "T-Shirt of the Month Club Plan",
  "description": "Template creation.",
  "type": "fixed",
  "payment_definitions": [
    {
      "name": "Regular Payments",
      "type": "REGULAR",
      "frequency": "MONTH",
      "frequency_interval": "2",
      "amount": {
        "value": "100",
        "currency": "USD"
      },
      "cycles": "12",
      "charge_models": [
        {
          "type": "SHIPPING",
          "amount": {
            "value": "10",
            "currency": "USD"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "TAX",
          "amount": {
            "value": "12",
            "currency": "USD"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "merchant_preferences": {
    "setup_fee": {
      "value": "1",
      "currency": "USD"
    },
    "return_url": "http://www.return.com",
    "cancel_url": "http://www.cancel.com",
    "auto_bill_amount": "YES",
    "initial_fail_amount_action": "CONTINUE",
    "max_fail_attempts": "0"
  }
}'
Response

Returns a plan object along with the state of the billing plan. The response includes a billing plan ID that uniquely identifies the plan.

id string
The ID of the billing plan.
Read only.

Maximum length: 128.

name string
The billing plan name.
Maximum length: 128.

description string
The billing plan description.
Maximum length: 128.

type enum
The billing plan type.
Possible values: FIXED, INFINITE.

Maximum length: 20.

state enum
The billing plan status.
Read only.

Possible values: CREATED, ACTIVE, INACTIVE, DELETED.

create_time string
The date and time when the billing plan was created, in YYYY-MM-DDTimeTimezone format as defined in ISO8601.
Read only.

update_time string
The date and time when the billing plan was updated, in YYYY-MM-DDTimeTimezone format as defined in ISO8601.
Read only.

payment_definitions array (contains the payment_definition object)
Resource that represents payment definition scheduling information.
terms array (contains the terms object)
Resource that represents the terms used by the plan.
Read only.

merchant_preferences object
Resource that represents the merchant preferences for a plan, such as max failed attempts, set up fee, and so on.
links array (contains the link object)
HATEOAS links related to this call.
Read only.


